As a further step, the propagation of the uncertainty from the pixel to the continental scale requires the assessment of the spatial correlation of the errors, otherwise per-pixel errors cancel out and the overall uncertainty may be largely underestimated. In the present case, standard use of spatial variograms (sensu ref.45) is precluded by the spatial patchiness of ROIs, the heterogeneity of biomass due to river dynamics and in addition, because it is computationally prohibitive (even when encoded in GEE). Following Ref.45, we therefore adopted two empirical autocorrelation length-scales (ALS) - ALS1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
